{0 Semantic Model}

The semantic model is split into three modules.

{1 Reactive Programs}

{!module-SpecV2.ReactiveModel} defines the extensional notion of reactive
program used in the development. One synchronous tick is total by construction
through the fields [select] and [select_enabled].

{1 Conditional Safety}

{!module-SpecV2.ConditionalSafety} adds the specification layer:

- an assumption automaton over inputs;
- a guarantee automaton over input/output observations;
- the semantic predicates [AvoidA] and [AvoidG].

{1 Explicit Product}

{!module-SpecV2.ExplicitProduct} synchronizes the program and both automata.
This is the level where global violations become local dangerous steps.
